Lab Questions CNT
UNIT 1
Unit-I Question 1a:
Set up a small wired network of 2–4 computers using Hub/Switch including preparation of cables.
Unit-I Question 1b:
Set up a small wireless network using an access point and perform networking commands:
ping, pathping, ipconfig/ifconfig, arp, netstat, nbtstat, nslookup, route, traceroute/tracert, nmap.

UNIT 2
Unit-II Question 2a:
Write a program to find the shortest path using Dijkstra’s algorithm for a given network graph.
Unit-II Question 2b:
Using the same network, generate OSPF-style routing table entries based on Link State Routing

UNIT 3
Unit-III Question 3a:
Write TCP and UDP client–server programs to exchange “Hello” messages and implement file transfer (TCP) and trigonometric calculator (UDP).
Unit-III Question 3b:
Capture Ethernet, IP, TCP, and UDP packets using Wireshark and analyze their headers.

UNIT 4
Unit-IV Question 4a:
Design a website using Bootstrap with toggleable/dynamic tabs or pills.
Unit-IV Question 4b:
Use jQuery to dynamically show sections: SDP, EDI, DT, and VIT course projects.

UNIT 5
Unit-V Question 5a:
Develop a responsive React frontend for entering MSE (30%) and ESE (70%) marks for four subjects.
Unit-V Question 5b:
Implement Spring Boot + MySQL/MongoDB/Oracle backend to compute and display semester results.

UNIT 6
Unit-VI Question 6a:
Design a responsive online bookstore (Home, Login, Catalogue, Registration) using React.
Unit-VI Question 6b:
Implement backend using Node.js/PHP with MySQL/MongoDB/Oracle for user authentication and book storage.

